headline: Why Oracle Stock Jumped 32% in June
summary: Oracle posted another quarter of impressive cloud infrastructure growth.  Shares of Oracle (NYSE: ORCL) were on the move last month as the legacy tech giant best known for database software continues to impress investors with its growth in cloud infrastructure, showing it's capitalizing on the artificial intelligence (AI) boom.  Oracle is still much smaller than the big three cloud computing players (Amazon, Alphabet, and Microsoft), but it's growing faster than them.
